(1) A railway company may, subject to the provisions of this Act— (a) determine the conditions upon which passengers and luggage shall be carried by it and different conditions may be determined in different cases; and such conditions shall be published in the Tariff Book and shall have effect from the date of such publication or from such later date as may be specified therein; (b) determine the fares and other charges for the carriage of passengers and luggage by it; and such fares and other charges shall be published in the Tariff Book and shall have effect from the date of such publication or from such later date as may be specified therein: Provided that provision shall be made for the carriage free of charge of a specified amount of baggage by a passenger , and different amounts may be determined for passengers travelling by different classes; (c) determine the different classes of accommodation available to passengers in its trains or vehicles.
