(1) A railway company shall not be liable for the loss of life of, or personal injury to, any passenger except where such loss of life or personal injury is caused by want of reasonable care, diligence or skill on the part of the railway company or of any of its employees or agents: Provided that nothing in this subsection shall impose upon the railway company any liability from which it is exempt under the provisions of this Act.
